...Assures APC would win the guber polls President Muhammadu Buhari Friday urged the ruling party, All Progressives Congress (APC), to work diligently and ensure fairness in electoral processes, while returning the governorship candidate of the party, Rotimi Akeredolu, SAN, for second term in office.  The President, who presented the party’s flag to the candidate at the Presidential Villa, Abuja said the reconciliation process in the state branch of the party had provided a solid ground for an easier clear victory for the candidate, assuring Akeredolu of the party’s full support.  Briefing State House Correspondent after Akeredolu's endorsement by Mr President, the APC, Caretaker Committee Chairman and Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni expressed hope that the ruling APC would win the election in Ondo state as the party will use all civil means to win the election.  Chairman of the APC Campaign Committee for the Ondo governorship election, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, said that the achievements of Akeredolu in the past four years has made his assignment easier.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that Governor Akeredolu on his part, noted that Mr. President's assurance will gear him to victory while he plans to do more for his state. 